  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nAnvil\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (7941935 2022-07-11T00:09:05.617669537Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nanvil\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nfoundry doesn't seem to implement [this part of eip-1559 specification](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/f6db72a05b8f5e4fe5ab24c38494dec6ff974a5f/EIPS/eip-1559.md?plain=1#L187-L194) correctly.\r\n\r\nif you fork from mainnet block 13184859 and replay the very first transaction from block 13184860, you'll get an error saying `{'code': -32003, 'message': 'max fee per gas less than block base fee'}`\r\n\r\nlooking into it further, you can see this:\r\n- block `number=13184859 gas_limit=29999972 gas_used=12257311 base_fee=63739886069`\r\n- block `number=13184860 gas_limit=30000000 gas_used=29996605 base_fee=62283069776`\r\n- transaction `maxFeePerGas: 62283069776 maxPriorityFeePerGas: 0` matches block 13184860 base fee\r\n\r\nbut foundry seems to compare it to values from 13184859, which is incorrect implementation.",
